## Plan: `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

### Context
The Mistral Instruct v0.3 format (`[INST] user [/INST] assistant</s>`) has no dedicated handler in `common/chat.cpp`. It differs from the already-handled Ministral 3 format precisely by the **absence** of `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` — Ministral 3 wraps system messages with `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]...[/SYSTEM_PROMPT]`, whereas v0.3 prepends the system text directly into the first `[INST]` block.

The "no header, no existing handler changes" constraint means everything goes in `common/chat.cpp` and a new Jinja file — no enum, no `src/llama-chat.h` changes needed.

---

### Files

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3.jinja` | **Create** |
| `common/chat.cpp` | **Add** handler function + detection `if`-block |
| `tests/test-chat.cpp` | **Add** `peg_tester` block |

